01:39:42.080 --> 01:39:44.450
GEORGE BARBASTATHIS: And
then the last one is actually

01:39:44.450 --> 01:39:46.730
the most interesting one.

01:39:46.730 --> 01:39:51.110
Because this law actually was
involved with a breakthrough

01:39:51.110 --> 01:39:52.940
in electromagnetics.

01:39:52.940 --> 01:40:05.380
It can be known for a long time
that if you have a current,

01:40:05.380 --> 01:40:07.880
a magnetic field develops
around that current.

01:40:07.880 --> 01:40:10.370
That is actually Lorentz--

01:40:10.370 --> 01:40:12.020
it is known as Lorentz force.

01:40:12.020 --> 01:40:17.420
If you have a moving charge,
and then you put a little magnet

01:40:17.420 --> 01:40:20.082
nearby, then the--

01:40:20.082 --> 01:40:21.680
what am I saying.

01:40:21.680 --> 01:40:23.180
Anyway, if you have
a moving charge,

01:40:23.180 --> 01:40:29.870
and if you have a current,
it creates a magnetic field

01:40:29.870 --> 01:40:30.370
around it.

01:40:30.370 --> 01:40:32.930
That has been known
for a long time.

01:40:32.930 --> 01:40:35.360
But what was not
known and was noticed

01:40:35.360 --> 01:40:41.790
by Maxwell was that if
you have a capacitor--

01:40:41.790 --> 01:40:44.590
well, in a capacitor, you can
not have a current per se.

01:40:44.590 --> 01:40:47.580
Because the capacitor, well,
inside there's a dielectric.

01:40:47.580 --> 01:40:49.800
So there can be no current.

01:40:49.800 --> 01:40:55.360
But you can have
a variable charge

01:40:55.360 --> 01:40:57.760
density in the capacitor plate.

01:40:57.760 --> 01:41:02.650
So what I'm trying to say
is that if you apply a--

01:41:02.650 --> 01:41:05.050
think of charge in a capacitor.

01:41:05.050 --> 01:41:10.660
When you charge a capacitor,
the capacitor, at the beginning,

01:41:10.660 --> 01:41:13.840
the voltage across
the capacitor is 0.

01:41:13.840 --> 01:41:15.820
And by the time you
have totally charged it,

01:41:15.820 --> 01:41:19.590
the voltage has
reached some value.

01:41:19.590 --> 01:41:22.560
Well, while the
voltage is changing,

01:41:22.560 --> 01:41:27.660
there is actually charge
flow into the capacitor.

01:41:27.660 --> 01:41:31.080
There is a positive charge
going to the positive electrode,

01:41:31.080 --> 01:41:36.600
then negative leaving from
the opposite electrode.

01:41:36.600 --> 01:41:38.280
And at the same time,
what is happening,

01:41:38.280 --> 01:41:40.860
the electric field inside
the capacitor grows.

01:41:40.860 --> 01:41:43.830
Because as you get more charge
accumulating in the capacitor

01:41:43.830 --> 01:41:48.340
plates, then the electric field
of the capacitor is changing.

01:41:48.340 --> 01:41:52.110
So in a sense, you can think
of it as a current as well.

01:41:52.110 --> 01:41:55.860
And what Maxwell-- he
guessed it, actually.

01:41:55.860 --> 01:41:58.770
He didn't observe it.

01:41:58.770 --> 01:42:00.300
But he guessed it.

01:42:00.300 --> 01:42:05.100
He guessed that this kind
of variable electric field

01:42:05.100 --> 01:42:09.160
should also generate
a magnetic field.

01:42:09.160 --> 01:42:12.120
And the only reason he
guessed it is by symmetry

01:42:12.120 --> 01:42:14.370
from the previous law.

01:42:14.370 --> 01:42:15.280
What does that say?

01:42:15.280 --> 01:42:19.020
It says that if you have
a variable magnetic flux,

01:42:19.020 --> 01:42:21.990
you generate an
electrical potential.

01:42:21.990 --> 01:42:23.700
Well, he looked
at this equation.

01:42:23.700 --> 01:42:25.070
And he said, wait a minute.

01:42:25.070 --> 01:42:27.350
It's fine that if I
have a moving charge,

01:42:27.350 --> 01:42:28.470
I have a magnetic field.

01:42:28.470 --> 01:42:29.370
OK, fine.

01:42:29.370 --> 01:42:31.080
But if also I have a moving--

01:42:31.080 --> 01:42:34.020
if I have a variable
potential, then why

01:42:34.020 --> 01:42:36.090
should I not generate
a magnetic field?

01:42:36.090 --> 01:42:37.890
I should.

01:42:37.890 --> 01:42:40.210
And it turned out to be true.

01:42:40.210 --> 01:42:43.900
I mean-- Maxwell,
by the way, he was--

01:42:43.900 --> 01:42:46.910
do you know what
was his day job?

01:42:46.910 --> 01:42:55.610
James Clerk Maxwell, he
was a fluid mechanic.

01:42:55.610 --> 01:42:57.640
He was [INAUDIBLE].

01:42:57.640 --> 01:43:00.670
And that's why the terminology--
not the terminology,

01:43:00.670 --> 01:43:03.270
but the notation in
electromagnetic magnetics

01:43:03.270 --> 01:43:07.150
is actually very similar to the
fluid mechanics notation, rho,

01:43:07.150 --> 01:43:08.513
and epsilon, and all that stuff.

01:43:08.513 --> 01:43:10.430
I mean, they're not the
same things, but the--

01:43:13.000 --> 01:43:18.500
and also, these theorems,
the mathematical theorems,

01:43:18.500 --> 01:43:20.660
they come from fluid mechanics.

01:43:20.660 --> 01:43:22.430
They apply to
incomprehensible flows.

01:43:22.430 --> 01:43:24.200
For example, the
Gauss theorem, it

01:43:24.200 --> 01:43:34.960
applies to incomprehensible
flow in the pressure potential.

01:43:34.960 --> 01:43:38.270
Anyway, so Maxwell
did that first.

01:43:38.270 --> 01:43:45.520
So he guessed that you should
have this form in here.

01:43:45.520 --> 01:43:47.860
And then he actually wrote
down all of these equations

01:43:47.860 --> 01:43:50.970
in a coordinated form.

01:43:50.970 --> 01:43:53.500
And the reason this was
a very valuable thing,

01:43:53.500 --> 01:43:58.340
and I guess we're all employed
because of this [INAUDIBLE],,

01:43:58.340 --> 01:44:02.803
is because if you manipulate
Maxwell's equations--

01:44:02.803 --> 01:44:04.970
and I will not do it now,
because I ran out of time.

01:44:04.970 --> 01:44:07.500
But if you manipulate
them, you can actually

01:44:07.500 --> 01:44:11.680
show that you arrive at the
wave equation for the electric

01:44:11.680 --> 01:44:12.880
or the magnetic field.

01:44:12.880 --> 01:44:14.710
I did it here for
the electric field.

01:44:14.710 --> 01:44:17.590
But you can also derive
the same equation

01:44:17.590 --> 01:44:19.267
for the magnetic field.

01:44:19.267 --> 01:44:21.100
So therefore, what this
means is that if you

01:44:21.100 --> 01:44:28.850
have electric and magnetic
fields which change in time,

01:44:28.850 --> 01:44:30.590
Maxwell's equations
tell you that they

01:44:30.590 --> 01:44:32.960
change in a coordinated way.

01:44:32.960 --> 01:44:36.890
And the way they change is
as an electromagnetic wave.

